\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Budget-threshold sensitivity analysis (SA1). Left: investment allocation by budget level. Below \$225K the optimizer concentrates entirely in Preventive Maintenance ($I_1$, blue); the yellow dashed line marks the \$225K diversification threshold where Risk-Based Targeting ($I_4$, purple) first enters the solution. Above \$225K allocation is mixed across $I_1$, $I_3$, and $I_4$. The black dashed line marks the \$1M board proposal. Right: expected utility $E[U(-C)]$ by budget with two traces: raw MC estimates (yellow) and a 9-point moving-average overlay (blue) to reveal the directional trend. Raw point-level variation remains non-monotonic. Seeded MC, 1{,}600 runs per point (SA1).}}{15}{figure.caption.12}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:sa1}{{4}{15}{Budget-threshold sensitivity analysis (SA1). Left: investment allocation by budget level. Below \$225K the optimizer concentrates entirely in Preventive Maintenance ($I_1$, blue); the yellow dashed line marks the \$225K diversification threshold where Risk-Based Targeting ($I_4$, purple) first enters the solution. Above \$225K allocation is mixed across $I_1$, $I_3$, and $I_4$. The black dashed line marks the \$1M board proposal. Right: expected utility $E[U(-C)]$ by budget with two traces: raw MC estimates (yellow) and a 9-point moving-average overlay (blue) to reveal the directional trend. Raw point-level variation remains non-monotonic. Seeded MC, 1{,}600 runs per point (SA1)}{figure.caption.12}{}}
